{"title_page": "Keszthely District", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Keszthely District\n| native_name            = <small>''Keszthelyi j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = HUN Keszthely C\u00edmer.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Keszthelyi j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Keszthely District within Hungary and Zala County.\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Zala County|Zala]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Keszthely]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 535.93\n| area_rank              = [[Zala County#Regional structure|4th in Zala]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 49,421\n|population_rank         = [[Zala County#Regional structure|3rd in Zala]]\n|population_density_km2  = 92\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Keszthely''' ({{lang-hu|Keszthelyi j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in eastern part of [[Zala County]]. ''[[Keszthely]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Western Transdanubia|Western Transdanubia Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKeszthely District borders with [[Zalaszentgr\u00f3t District]] and [[S\u00fcmeg District]] ''([[Veszpr\u00e9m County]])'' to the north, [[Tapolca District]] ''(Veszpr\u00e9m County)'' to the east, [[Marcali District]] ''([[Somogy County]])'' and [[Nagykanizsa District]] to the south, [[Zalaegerszeg District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Keszthely District is '''30'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]], '''2''' large villages and '''26''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref name=\"ksh\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls|website=ksh.hu|title=A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve|accessdate=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Als\u00f3p\u00e1hok]] (1,360)\n*[[Balatongy\u00f6r\u00f6k]] (1,021)\n*[[B\u00f3kah\u00e1za]] (286)\n*[[Cserszegtomaj]] (2,792)\n*[[Di\u00f3sk\u00e1l]] (474)\n*[[Egeraracsa]] (310)\n*[[Eszterg\u00e1lyhorv\u00e1ti]] (454)\n*[[Fels\u0151p\u00e1hok]] (635)\n*[[G\u00e9tye]] (117)\n*''[[Gyenesdi\u00e1s]]'' (3,568)\n*'''[[H\u00e9v\u00edz]]''' (4,663)\n*[[Karmacs]] (822)\n*'''[[Keszthely]]''' (20,382) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Ligetfalva]] (56)\n*[[Nemesb\u00fck]] (681)\n*[[Rezi]] (1,184)\n*[[S\u00e1rmell\u00e9k]] (1,829)\n*[[Szentgy\u00f6rgyv\u00e1r]] (298)\n*[[V\u00e1llus]] (135)\n*[[V\u00e1rv\u00f6lgy]] (1,041)\n*[[Vindornyafok]] (123)\n*[[Vindornyalak]] (81)\n*[[Vindornyasz\u0151l\u0151s]] (327)\n*''[[Vonyarcvashegy]]'' (2,178)\n*[[Zalaap\u00e1ti]] (1,654)\n*[[Zalacs\u00e1ny]] (970)\n*[[Zalak\u00f6vesk\u00fat]] (27)\n*[[Zalasz\u00e1nt\u00f3]] (965)\n*[[Zalaszentm\u00e1rton]] (65)\n*[[Zalav\u00e1r]] (886)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities, ''italics'' municipalities are large villages.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns in Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/keszthelyi-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Keszthely District]\n\n{{Keszthely District}}\n{{Districts of Zala County}}\n\n{{coord missing|Hungary}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Zala County]]\n\n\n{{Zala-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are avai