 Keszthely District is '''30'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]], '''2''' large villages and '''26''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref name=\"ksh\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls|website=ksh.hu|title=A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve|accessdate=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Als\u00f3p\u00e1hok]] (1,360)\n*[[Balatongy\u00f6r\u00f6k]] (1,021)\n*[[B\u00f3kah\u00e1za]] (286)\n*[[Cserszegtomaj]] (2,792)\n*[[Di\u00f3sk\u00e1l]] (474)\n*[[Egeraracsa]] (310)\n*[[Eszterg\u00e1lyhorv\u00e1ti]] (454)\n*[[Fels\u0151p\u00e1hok]] (635)\n*[[G\u00e9tye]] (117)\n*''[[Gyenesdi\u00e1s]]'' (3,568)\n*'''[[H\u00e9v\u00edz]]''' (4,663)\n*[[Karmacs]] (822)\n*'''[[Keszthely]]''' (20,382) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Ligetfalva]] (56)\n*[[Nemesb\u00fck]] (681)\n*[[Rezi]] (1,184)\n*[[S\u00e1rmell\u00e9k]] (1,829)\n*[[Szentgy\u00f6rgyv\u00e1r]] (298)\n*[[V\u00e1llus]] (135)\n*[[V\u00e1rv\u00f6lgy]] (1,041)\n*[[Vindornyafok]] (123)\n*[[Vindornyalak]] (81)\n*[[Vindornyasz\u0151l\u0151s]] (327)\n*''[[Vonyarcvashegy]]'' (2,178)\n*[[Zalaap\u00e1ti]] (1,654)\n*[[Zalacs\u00e1ny]] (970)\n*[[Zalak\u00f6vesk\u00fat]] (27)\n*[[Zalasz\u00e1nt\u00f3]] (965)\n*[[Zalaszentm\u00e1rton]] (65)\n*[[Zalav\u00e1r]] (886)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities, ''italics'' municipalities are large villages.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns in Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/keszthelyi-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Keszthely District]\n\n{{Keszthely District}}\n{{Districts of Zala County}}\n\n{{coord missing|Hungary}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Zala County]]\n\n{{Zala-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keszthely_District"}
{"title_page": "Kemecse District", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kemecse District\n| native_name            = <small>''Kemecsei j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image                = Kemecse2019jaras.jpg\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = HUN Kemecse C\u00edmer1.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Kemecsei j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Kemecse District within Hungary and Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County|Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Kemecse]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 246.41\n| area_rank              = [[Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County#Regional structure|12th in Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 22,066\n|population_rank         = [[Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County#Regional structure|10th in Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg]]\n|population_density_km2  = 90\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Kemecse''' ({{lang-hu|Kemecsei j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in central part of [[Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County]]. ''[[Kemecse]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Northern Great Plain|Northern Great Plain Statistical Region]]. This district is a part of [[R\u00e9tk\u00f6z]] geographical region.\n\n== Geography ==\nKemecse District borders with [[Kisv\u00e1rda District]] to the northeast, [[Baktal\u00f3r\u00e1nth\u00e1za District]] to the southeast, [[Ny\u00edregyh\u00e1za District]] to the south, [[Ibr\u00e1ny District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Kemecse District is '''11'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''9''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Berkesz]] (855)\n*[[Beszterec]] (1,086)\n*'''[[Demecser]]''' (4,284)\n*[[G\u00e9g\u00e9ny]] (1,975)\n*[[K\u00e9k]] (1,966)\n*'''[[Kemecse]]''' (4,792) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Ny\u00edrbogd\u00e1ny]] (2,861)\n*[[Ny\u00edrt\u00e9t]] (1,088)\n*[[Sz\u00e9kely (village)|Sz\u00e9kely]] (1,046)\n*[[Tiszar\u00e1d]] (568)\n*[[Vasmegyer]] (1,664)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kemecse District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value1 = 37.9\n|color1 = DodgerBlue\n|label2 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value2 = 0.4\n|color2 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label3 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value3 = 24.7\n|color3 = DarkOrchid\n|label4 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value4 = 8.1\n|color4 = MediumOrchid\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 1.6\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 5.3\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 0.2\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 21.8\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 22,066 and the [[population density]] was 90/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kemecsei \"Kemecsei j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 22,066\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minority is the Roma (approx. 2,000).\n\nTotal population (2011 census): 22,066<br>\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>4.1.6.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g nemzetis\u00e9g szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_15]''</ref> Identified themselves: 21,663 persons:\n*[[Hungarians]]: 19,597 (90.46%)\n*[[Romani people in Hungary|Gypsies]]: 1,900 (8.77%)\n*Others and indefinable: 166 (0.77%)\nApprox. 500 persons in Kemecse District did not declare their ethnic group at the 2011 census.\n\n===Religion===\nReligious adherence in the county according to 2011 census:<ref>4.1.7.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g vall\u00e1s, felekezet szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_15]''</ref>\n\n*[[Reformed Church in Hungary|Reformed]] \u2013 8,356;\n*Catholic \u2013 7,241 ([[Roman Catholicism in Hungary|Roman Catholic]] \u2013 5,443; [[Hungarian Greek Catholic Church|Greek Catholic]] \u2013 1,798);\n*[[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Hungary|Evangelical]] \u2013 92;\n*other religions \u2013 360;\n*[[Irreligion|Non-religious]] \u2013 1,175; \n*[[Atheism]] \u2013 55;\n*''Undeclared'' \u2013 4,787.\n\n==Gallery==\n<center>\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"200px\" perrow=\"4\">\nFile:Berkesz.jpg|Aerial view of [[Berkesz]]\nFile:House from Beszterec.jpg|Traditional house from [[Beszterec]]\nFile:Berkesz kast\u00e9ly.jpg|Vay Mansion in Berkesz\nFile:Sz\u00e9kely l\u00e9gifot\u00f3.jpg|Aerial view of [[Sz\u00e9kely (village)|Sz\u00e9kely]]\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns of Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/kemecsei-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Kemecse District]\n\n{{Kemecse District}}\n{{Districts of Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County}}\n\n{{coord missing|Hungary}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County]]\n\n\n{{Szabolcs-geo-stub}}\n", "tex