s with [[Kisv\u00e1rda District]] to the northeast, [[Baktal\u00f3r\u00e1nth\u00e1za District]] to the southeast, [[Ny\u00edregyh\u00e1za District]] to the south, [[Ibr\u00e1ny District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Kemecse District is '''11'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''9''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Berkesz]] (855)\n*[[Beszterec]] (1,086)\n*'''[[Demecser]]''' (4,284)\n*[[G\u00e9g\u00e9ny]] (1,975)\n*[[K\u00e9k]] (1,966)\n*'''[[Kemecse]]''' (4,792) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Ny\u00edrbogd\u00e1ny]] (2,861)\n*[[Ny\u00edrt\u00e9t]] (1,088)\n*[[Sz\u00e9kely (village)|Sz\u00e9kely]] (1,046)\n*[[Tiszar\u00e1d]] (568)\n*[[Vasmegyer]] (1,664)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kemecse District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value1 = 37.9\n|color1 = DodgerBlue\n|label2 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value2 = 0.4\n|color2 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label3 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value3 = 24.7\n|color3 = DarkOrchid\n|label4 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value4 = 8.1\n|color4 = MediumOrchid\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 1.6\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 5.3\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 0.2\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 21.8\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 22,066 and the [[population density]] was 90/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kemecsei \"Kemecsei j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 22,066\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minority is 