{"title_page": "Kecskem\u00e9t District", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kecskem\u00e9t District\n| native_name            = <small>''Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = Kecskem\u00e9t flag.png\n|image_blank_emblem   = Coa Hungary Town Kecskem\u00e9t.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Kecskem\u00e9t District within Hungary and B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County|B\u00e1cs-Kiskun]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Kecskem\u00e9t]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 1,212.21\n| area_rank              = [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County#Regional structure|1st in B\u00e1cs-Kiskun]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 155,481\n|population_rank         = [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County#Regional structure|1st in B\u00e1cs-Kiskun]]\n|population_density_km2  = 128\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Kecskem\u00e9t''' ({{lang-hu|Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in northern part of [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County]]. ''[[Kecskem\u00e9t]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Southern Great Plain|Southern Great Plain Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKecskem\u00e9t District borders with [[Dabas District]] and [[Cegl\u00e9d District]] ''([[Pest County]])'' to the north, [[Nagyk\u0151r\u00f6s District]] ''(Pest County)'' to the northeast, [[Tiszak\u00e9cske District]] to the east, [[Kiskunf\u00e9legyh\u00e1za District]] to the south, [[Kisk\u0151r\u00f6s District]] and [[Kunszentmikl\u00f3s District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Kecskem\u00e9t District is '''16'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''1''' [[Town with county rights|urban county]], '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''13''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2014)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2014.xls A KSH 2014. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[\u00c1gasegyh\u00e1za]] (1,892)\n*[[Ball\u00f3sz\u00f6g]] (3,366)\n*[[Fels\u0151lajos]] (858)\n*[[F\u00fcl\u00f6ph\u00e1za]] (845)\n*[[F\u00fcl\u00f6pjakab]] (1,161)\n*[[Helv\u00e9cia]] (4,406)\n*[[Jakabsz\u00e1ll\u00e1s]] (2,615)\n*'''[[Kecskem\u00e9t]]''' (112,071) \u2013 district and county seat\n*'''[[Kerekegyh\u00e1za]]''' (6,330)\n*[[Kunbaracs]] (615)\n*[[Kunsz\u00e1ll\u00e1s]] (1,661)\n*[[Lad\u00e1nybene]] (1,574)\n*'''[[Lajosmizse]]''' (11,228)\n*[[Ny\u00e1rl\u0151rinc]] (2,323)\n*[[Orgov\u00e1ny]] (3,372)\n*[[V\u00e1rosf\u00f6ld]] (2,158)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kecskem\u00e9t District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value1 = 45.0\n|color1 = DarkOrchid\n|label2 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value2 = 0.3\n|color2 = MediumOrchid\n|label3 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value3 = 10.2\n|color3 = DodgerBlue\n|label4 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value4 = 1.0\n|color4 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 1.6\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 14.0\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 1.2\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 26.7\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 155,481 and the [[population density]] was 128/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kecskemeti \"Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 155,481\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minorities are the German and Roma (approx. 1,750), Romanian (700), Croat (150), Russian and Serb (200), Slovak, Bulgarian and Ukrainian (100).\n\nTotal population (2011 census): 155,481<br>\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>4.1.6.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g nemzetis\u00e9g szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_03]''</ref> Identified themselves: 141,203 persons:\n*[[Hungarians]]: 134,683 (95.38%)\n*[[Germans of Hungary|Germans]]: 1,748 (1.24%)\n*[[Romani people in Hungary|Gypsies]]: 1,734 (1.23%)\n*Others and indefinable: 3,038 (2.15%)\nApprox. 14,000 persons in Kecskem\u00e9t District did not declare their ethnic group at the 2011 census.\n\n===Religion===\nReligious adherence in the county according to 2011 census:<ref>4.1.7.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g vall\u00e1s, felekezet szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_03]''</ref>\n\n*Catholic \u2013 70,482 ([[Roman Catholicism in Hungary|Roman Catholic]] \u2013 70,032; [[Hungarian Greek Catholic Church|Greek Catholic]] \u2013 424);\n*[[Reformed Church in Hungary|Reformed]] \u2013 15,788;\n*[[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Hungary|Evangelical]] \u2013 1,575;\n*other religions \u2013 2,494; \n*[[Irreligion|Non-religious]] \u2013 21,788; \n*[[Atheism]] \u2013 1,887;\n*''Undeclared'' \u2013 41,467.\n\n==Gallery==\n<center>\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"200px\" perrow=\"4\">\nFile:V\u00e1rosi Tan\u00e1csh\u00e1z (2253. sz\u00e1m\u00fa m\u0171eml\u00e9k) 4.jpg|Downtown of [[Kecskem\u00e9t]]\nFile:Kerekegyh\u00e1za1.jpg|Aerial view of [[Kerekegyh\u00e1za]]\nFile:Lajosmizsei Tanyam\u00fazeum (\u00f3lak kamr\u00e1val) 20130929 370.JPG|Farm Museum in [[Lajosmizse]]\nFile:V\u00e1rosf\u00f6ld l\u00e9gifot\u00f3.jpg|Aerial view of [[V\u00e1rosf\u00f6ld]]\nFile:Cifra Palota.jpg|[[Cifra Palace]] in Kecskem\u00e9t\nFile:Kecskem\u00e9t kil\u00e1t\u00e1s.jpg|M\u0171kertv\u00e1ros district of Kecskem\u00e9t\nFile:Katona J\u00f3zsef Sz\u00ednh\u00e1z (Kecskem\u00e9t).jpg|Katona J\u00f3zsef Theater (Kecskem\u00e9t)\nFile:Megyesz\u00e9khelyek - B\u00e1cs-Kiskun megye - Kecskem\u00e9t.jpg|Aerial view of Kecskem\u00e9t\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns of Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/kecskemeti-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Kecskem\u00e9t District]\n\n{{Kecskem\u00e9t District}}\n{{Districts of B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County}}\n\n{{coord|46.8833|N|19.7000|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County]]\n\n\n{{Bacs-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kecskem\u00e9t District\n| native_name            = <small>''Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = Kecskem\u00e9t flag.png\n|image_blank_emblem   = Coa Hungary Town Kecskem\u00e9t.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Kecskem\u00e9ti j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Kecskem\u00e9t District within Hungary and B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[B\u00e1cs-Kiskun County|B\u00e1cs-Kiskun]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Kecskem\u00e9t]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_o