{"title_page": "Kazincbarcika District", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kazincbarcika District\n| native_name            = <small>''Kazincbarcikai j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = HUN Kazincbarcika C\u00edmer.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Kazincbarcikai j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Kazincbarcika District within Hungary and Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n County|Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Kazincbarcika]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 341.70\n| area_rank              = [[Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n County#Regional structure|12th in Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 66,470\n|population_rank         = [[Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n County#Regional structure|2nd in Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n]]\n|population_density_km2  = 193\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Kazincbarcika''' ({{lang-hu|Kazincbarcikai j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in north-western part of [[Borsod-Aba\u00faj-Zempl\u00e9n County]]. ''[[Kazincbarcika]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Northern Hungary|Northern Hungary Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKazincbarcika District borders with [[Edel\u00e9ny District]] northeast, [[Miskolc District]] to the southeast, [[B\u00e9lap\u00e1tfalva District]] ''([[Heves County]])'' to the southwest, [[\u00d3zd District]] to the west, [[Putnok District]] to the northwest. The number of the inhabited places in Kazincbarcika District is '''22'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''3''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|town]], '''2''' large villages and '''17''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2012)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2012.xls A KSH 2012. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Alacska]] (748)\n*[[Als\u00f3telekes]] (135)\n*[[B\u00e1nhorv\u00e1ti]] (1,335)\n*[[Berente]] (1,117)\n*[[D\u00e9destapolcs\u00e1ny]] (1,426)\n*[[Fels\u0151telekes]] (683)\n*''[[Izs\u00f3falva]]'' (1,739)\n*'''[[Kazincbarcika]]''' (28,664) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Kurity\u00e1n]] (1,598)\n*[[M\u00e1lyinka]] (475)\n*''[[M\u00facsony]]'' (3,095)\n*[[Nagybarca]] (1,049)\n*[[Ormosb\u00e1nya]] (1,670)\n*'''[[Rudab\u00e1nya]]''' (2,488)\n*[[Rudolftelep]] (714)\n*[[Saj\u00f3galg\u00f3c]] (365)\n*[[Saj\u00f3iv\u00e1nka]] (605)\n*[[Saj\u00f3kaza]] (3,403)\n*'''[[Saj\u00f3szentp\u00e9ter]]''' (11,965)\n*[[Szuhak\u00e1ll\u00f3]] (946)\n*[[Tardona]] (1,011)\n*[[Vadna]] (597)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities, ''italics'' municipalities are large villages.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kazincbarcika District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value1 = 25.8\n|color1 = DarkOrchid\n|label2 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value2 = 5.2\n|color2 = MediumOrchid\n|label3 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value3 = 21.4\n|color3 = DodgerBlue\n|label4 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value4 = 0.6\n|color4 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 1.7\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 19.3\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 1.2\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 24.8\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 66,470 and the [[population density]] was 195/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kazincbarcikai \"Kazincbarcikai j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 66,470\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minorities are the Roma (approx. 4,000), German (350), Polish and Rusyn (150).\n\nTotal population (2011 census): 66,470<br>\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>4.1.6.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g nemzetis\u00e9g szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_05]''</ref> Identified themselves: 63,350 persons:\n*[[Hungarians]]: 58,247 (91.94%)\n*[[Romani people in Hungary|Gypsies]]: 3,919 (6.18%)\n*Others and indefinable: 1,184 (1.87%)\nApprox. 3,000 persons in Kazincbarcika District did not declare their ethnic group at the 2011 census.\n\n===Religion===\nReligious adherence in the county according to 2011 census:<ref>4.1.7.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g vall\u00e1s, felekezet szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_05]''</ref>\n\n*Catholic \u2013 20,582 ([[Roman Catholicism in Hungary|Roman Catholic]] \u2013 17,135; [[Hungarian Greek Catholic Church|Greek Catholic]] \u2013 3,444);\n*[[Reformed Church in Hungary|Reformed]] \u2013 14,222;\n*[[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Hungary|Evangelical]] \u2013 422;\n*other religions \u2013 1,167; \n*[[Irreligion|Non-religious]] \u2013 12,810; \n*[[Atheism]] \u2013 790;\n*''Undeclared'' \u2013 16,477.\n\n==Gallery==\n<center>\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"200px\" perrow=\"4\">\nFile:Sz\u0151ke G\u00e1bor Mikl\u00f3s \u2013 Unikornis.jpg|[[Kazincbarcika]], the ''district seat''\nFile:Civertanlegifotorudabanya3.jpg|Aerial view of [[Rudab\u00e1nya]]\nFile:Kurity\u00e1n - Palace.jpg|Pallavicini Mansion in [[Kurity\u00