{"title_page": "Kapuv\u00e1r District", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kapuv\u00e1r District\n| native_name            = <small>''Kapuv\u00e1ri j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = HUN Kapuv\u00e1r C\u00edmer.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Kapuv\u00e1ri j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Kapuv\u00e1r District within Hungary and Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County.\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County|Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Kapuv\u00e1r]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 372.14\n| area_rank              = [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County#Regional structure|5th in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 23,778\n|population_rank         = [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County#Regional structure|5th in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]]\n|population_density_km2  = 64\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Kapuv\u00e1r''' ({{lang-hu|Kapuv\u00e1ri j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in central-western part of [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]]. ''[[Kapuv\u00e1r]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Western Transdanubia|Western Transdanubia Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKapuv\u00e1r District borders with the [[Austria]]n state of [[Burgenland]] to the north, [[Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r District]] and [[Csorna District]] to the east, [[Celld\u00f6m\u00f6lk District]] and [[S\u00e1rv\u00e1r District]] ''([[Vas County]])'' to the south, [[Sopron District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Kapuv\u00e1r District is '''19'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''17''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2012)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2012.xls A KSH 2012. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Bab\u00f3t]] (1,097)\n*'''[[Beled]]''' (2,553)\n*[[Cir\u00e1k]] (568)\n*[[D\u00e9nesfa]] (363)\n*[[Edve]] (106)\n*[[Gy\u00f3r\u00f3]] (419)\n*[[Himod]] (595)\n*[[H\u00f6vej]] (313)\n*'''[[Kapuv\u00e1r]]''' (10,353) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Kisfalud]] (730)\n*[[Mih\u00e1lyi]] (1,051)\n*[[Osli]] (856)\n*[[R\u00e1bakec\u00f6l]] (665)\n*[[R\u00e9pceszemere]] (256)\n*[[Sz\u00e1rf\u00f6ld]] (897)\n*[[Vadosfa]] (75)\n*[[V\u00e1s\u00e1rosfalu]] (157)\n*[[Veszk\u00e9ny]] (913)\n*[[Vitny\u00e9d]] (1,359)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kapuv\u00e1r District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value1 = 71.3\n|color1 = DarkOrchid\n|label2 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value2 = 0.1\n|color2 = MediumOrchid\n|label3 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value3 = 5.4\n|color3 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label4 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value4 = 1.1\n|color4 = DodgerBlue\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 0.7\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 2.3\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 0.4\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 18.7\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 23,778 and the [[population density]] was 64/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kapuvari \"Kapuv\u00e1ri j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 23,778\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minorities are the Roma and German (approx. 300-300).\n\nTotal population (2011 census): 23,778<br>\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>4.1.6.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g nemzetis\u00e9g szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_08]''</ref> Identified themselves: 21,806 persons:\n*[[Hungarians]]: 21,030 (96.44%)\n*[[Romani people in Hungary|Gypsies]]: 318 (1.46%)\n*[[Germans of Hungary|Germans]]: 297 (1.36%)\n*Others and indefinable: 161 (0.74%)\nApprox. 2,000 persons in Kapuv\u00e1r District did not declare their ethnic group at the 2011 census.\n\n===Religion===\nReligious adherence in the county according to 2011 census:<ref>4.1.7.1 A n\u00e9pess\u00e9g vall\u00e1s, felekezet szerint, 2011, {{in lang|hu}} ''[http://www.ksh.hu/nepszamlalas/tablak_teruleti_08]''</ref>\n\n*Catholic \u2013 16,983 ([[Roman Catholicism in Hungary|Roman Catholic]] \u2013 16,948; [[Hungarian Greek Catholic Church|Greek Catholic]] \u2013 31);\n*[[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Hungary|Evangelical]] \u2013 1,298; \n*[[Reformed Church in Hungary|Reformed]] \u2013 253;\n*other religions \u2013 157; \n*[[Irreligion|Non-religious]] \u2013 546; \n*[[Atheism]] \u2013 101;\n*''Undeclared'' \u2013 4,440.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns in Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/kapuvari-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Kapuv\u00e1r District]\n\n{{Kapuv\u00e1r District}}\n{{Districts of Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County}}\n\n{{coord missing|Hungary}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]]\n\n\n{{Gyor-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Kapuv\u00e1r D