ct]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Kapuv\u00e1r District is '''19'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''2''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|towns]] and '''17''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2012)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2012.xls A KSH 2012. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Bab\u00f3t]] (1,097)\n*'''[[Beled]]''' (2,553)\n*[[Cir\u00e1k]] (568)\n*[[D\u00e9nesfa]] (363)\n*[[Edve]] (106)\n*[[Gy\u00f3r\u00f3]] (419)\n*[[Himod]] (595)\n*[[H\u00f6vej]] (313)\n*'''[[Kapuv\u00e1r]]''' (10,353) \u2013 district seat\n*[[Kisfalud]] (730)\n*[[Mih\u00e1lyi]] (1,051)\n*[[Osli]] (856)\n*[[R\u00e1bakec\u00f6l]] (665)\n*[[R\u00e9pceszemere]] (256)\n*[[Sz\u00e1rf\u00f6ld]] (897)\n*[[Vadosfa]] (75)\n*[[V\u00e1s\u00e1rosfalu]] (157)\n*[[Veszk\u00e9ny]] (913)\n*[[Vitny\u00e9d]] (1,359)\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipalities are cities.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Kapuv\u00e1r District (2011 census)\n|label1 = [[Catholic Church]]\n|value1 = 71.3\n|color1 = DarkOrchid\n|label2 = [[Greek Catholicism]]\n|value2 = 0.1\n|color2 = MediumOrchid\n|label3 = [[Lutheranism]]\n|value3 = 5.4\n|color3 = DeepSkyBlue\n|label4 = [[Calvinism]]\n|value4 = 1.1\n|color4 = DodgerBlue\n|label5 = Other religions\n|value5 = 0.7\n|color5 = Chartreuse\n|label6 = [[Irreligion|Non-religious]]\n|value6 = 2.3\n|color6 = Honeydew\n|label7 = [[Atheism|Atheists]]\n|value7 = 0.4\n|color7 = Grey\n|label8 = Undeclared\n|value8 = 18.7\n|color8 = Black\n}}\nIn 2011, it had a population of 23,778 and the [[population density]] was 64/km\u00b2.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>n\u00e9pess\u00e9g.com, ''[http://nepesseg.com/jaras/kapuvari \"Kapuv\u00e1ri j\u00e1r\u00e1s n\u00e9pess\u00e9ge\"]''</ref>\n! Change\n|-\n| 2011\n| 23,778\n|align=\"right\"| n/a\n|}\n\n===Ethnicity===\nBesides the Hungarian majority, the main minorities are the R